  "prompt": "What are the best Malayalam movies?",
  "response": "Malayalam cinema, often referred to as Mollywood, has produced numerous critically acclaimed and commercially successful films over the years. Here are some of the best Malayalam movies that have left a significant impact on audiences and critics alike:\n\n### Classic Malayalam Movies\n1. **Chemmeen (1965)** - Directed by Ramu Kariat, this film is a landmark in Indian cinema, blending a poignant love story with the lives of fishermen.\n2. **Pazhassi Raja (2009)** - Directed by Hariharan, this epic historical film stars Mammootty as the titular character, a warrior king who fought against the British.\n\n### Contemporary Malayalam Movies\n3. **Drishyam (2013)** - Directed by Jeethu Joseph, this thriller starring Mohanlal became a cultural phenomenon and has been remade in several languages.\n4. **Premam (2015)** - Directed by Alphonse Puthren, this coming-of-age romantic drama starring Nivin Pauly was a massive hit and praised for its screenplay and music.\n5. **Maheshinte Prathikaaram (2016)** - Directed by Dileesh Pothan, this film starring Fahadh Faasil is a quirky take on revenge and rural life.\n6. **Kumbalangi Nights (2019)** - Directed by Madhu C. Narayanan, this film explores familial relationships and mental health with a stellar cast including Fahadh Faasil and Soubin Shahir.\n\n### Critically Acclaimed Films\n7. **Peranbu (2018)** - Directed by Ram, this film features Mammootty in a powerful role as a father caring for his daughter with cerebral palsy.\n8. **Ee.Ma.Yau. (2018)** - Directed by Lijo Jose Pellissery, this dark comedy set during a funeral is noted for its unique narrative style.\n9. **Thondimuthalum Driksakshiyum (2017)** - Directed by Dileesh Pothan, this film is a gripping tale of a petty theft and its repercussions, starring Fahadh Faasil and Suraj Venjaramoodu.\n\n### Socially Relevant Films\n10. **Jallikattu (2019)** - Directed by Lijo Jose Pellissery, this film is a powerful commentary on human savagery and has been India\u2019s official entry for the Oscars.\n11. **Ayyapanum Koshiyum (2020)** - Directed by Sachy, this action drama starring Prithviraj Sukumaran and Biju Menon is a gripping narrative of conflict and power dynamics.\n\n### Family and Comedy Films\n12. **Bangalore Days (2014)** - Directed by Anjali Menon, this film follows the lives of three cousins in Bangalore and is a feel-good story with a strong emotional core.\n13. **Varathan (2018)** - Directed by Amal Neerad, this thriller stars Fahadh Faasil and Aishwarya Lekshmi and is known for its intense storytelling and cinematography.\n\nThese films represent a broad spectrum of genres and storytelling styles, showcasing the versatility and depth of Malayalam cinema. Whether you're looking for intense dramas, light-hearted comedies, or thought-provoking narratives, Malayalam cinema has something for everyone.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
